'''''Goody''''' is a [[platform game]] developed by [[Gonzalo Suárez Girard]] and released in 1987 by the Spanish company [[Opera Soft]]. The game was released for [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Amstrad PCW]], [[MSX]], [[ZX Spectrum]], and for [[MS-DOS]] compatible computers.

''Goody'' was the first video game by the Spanish designer Gonzalo Suárez Girard, who went on to make ''[[Commandos: Behind Enemy Lines]]''.<ref name=espanol>{{cite web | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925112947/https://www.elespanol.com/videojuegos/20160201/98990345_0.html | url=https://www.elespanol.com/videojuegos/20160201/98990345_0.html | title=Así cambió el cuento en el mundo de los videojuegos españoles | author=Sánchez, Víctor | date=February 2, 2016 | work=[[El Espanol]] | language=Spanish | archivedate=September 25, 2020 | url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=machina>{{cite web | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925112717/http://deusexmachina.es/entrevista-a-gonzo-suarez-desarrollador-de-videojuegos/ | url=http://deusexmachina.es/entrevista-a-gonzo-suarez-desarrollador-de-videojuegos/ | title=Entrevista a Gonzo Suarez, desarrollador de videojuegos | author=Suarez, Ricardo | date=October 9, 2014 | work=Deus Ex Machina | language=Spanish | archivedate=September 25, 2020 | url-status=live}}</ref>

==Plot==
[[Image:Goody.png|thumb|left|Four-color MS-DOS version]]
As an experienced thief John Nelson Brainner Stravinsky, known as Goody, has a mission to break into the [[Bank of Spain]]. Equipped with a ladder, Goody explores sewers and city buildings. Along the way he may collect treasure needed to purchase tools such as dynamite or a drill and to find out the access code to the main vault. Goody has to tackle many objects and enemies that try to stop him, such as remote-controlled combat helicopters, vipers, gorillas, the policeman Rodríguez, ghosts, and the evil Moon.

==Legacy==
''Goody The Remake'' was released by Coptron Game Studios in 2007 for [[Microsoft Windows]] and [[Linux]], and is now also available on [[Game Jolt]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://gamejolt.com/games/goody-the-remake-il-ladro/18208 | title=Goody The Remake (Il Ladro) by Coptron Game Studios - Game Jolt}}</ref>

An [[Isometric video game graphics|isometric]] spin-off game titled ''Goody Returns'' was published by eBrain Mobile in 2007.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://computeremuzone.com/ficha/1594/goody-returns&sec=mobile&l=en | title=Goody Returns - Mobile Zone}}</ref>

''Goody'' was re-released on Steam in March 2023.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://store.steampowered.com/app/1879530/Retro_Golden_Age__Goody/ | title=Retro Golden Age - Goody on Steam}}</ref>

